stateDiagram-v2
    classDef okState fill:#dce7f2,stroke:#2e5f8a,stroke-width:1.5px,color:#1f2933
    classDef offState fill:#e8eaed,stroke:#6b7480,color:#1f2933
    classDef declState fill:#f2f4f7,stroke:#52606d,stroke-dasharray:4 3,color:#1f2933

    state "NOT_ENROLLED" as NE
    state "PENDING" as PEN
    state "ENROLLED" as ENR
    state "FAILED" as FAIL
    state "REVOKED" as REV
    state "EXPIRED" as EXP

    [*] --> NE : enrollment row created<br/>(builder default)

    NE --> PEN : startEnrollment()<br/>async methods — FACE, VOICE, TOTP, ...
    NE --> ENR : startEnrollment(), auto-complete types<br/>(PASSWORD, NFC after card verify)

    PEN --> ENR : completeEnrollment(data,<br/>quality_score, liveness_score)
    PEN --> FAIL : failEnrollment()

    ENR --> PEN : re-enroll / optimize<br/>(startEnrollment on existing row)
    ENR --> REV : revokeEnrollment()<br/>user/admin removal or health reconcile<br/>(sets revoked_at)
    ENR --> EXP : expire()

    FAIL --> PEN : retry (startEnrollment)
    REV --> PEN : re-enroll (startEnrollment)
    EXP --> PEN : re-enroll (startEnrollment)

    note right of ENR
        Only ENROLLED satisfies isEnrolled() —
        the state the login engine and the
        default-flow lockout guardrail read.
        WebAuthn/passkey first use auto-binds
        a row directly to ENROLLED.
    end note

    note right of EXP
        expires_at column + transition exist;
        no scheduled sweep calls expire()
        on current main (declared path).
    end note

    class ENR okState
    class FAIL offState
    class REV offState
    class EXP declState
